.TH QIFTOP 1 "2026-06-10" "qiftop 0.2.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
qiftop \- Qt6 real\-time network traffic monitor (per\-interface and per\-connection)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qiftop
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qiftop
is a graphical, iftop\-style network monitor. It shows two live views:
.IP \(bu 3
.B Interfaces
\(em per\-interface throughput (RX/TX rate and cumulative totals), link
state, MTU, addresses and error/drop counters.
.IP \(bu 3
.B Connections
\(em per\-flow throughput for every active connection (the conntrack
table), with direction inference, reverse\-DNS, and optional grouping by
interface, process or container.
.PP
On startup qiftop probes for the privileged
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
on the system D\-Bus and, when reachable, consumes statistics from it as an
unprivileged client so the GUI never touches the kernel. When the agent is
not installed or the user lacks access (see
.B SECURITY
in
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)),
qiftop falls back to an in\-process capture backend, offering to relaunch
itself with elevated privileges via
.BR pkexec (1)
or
.BR sudo (8).
The active source ("agent <version>" vs. "in\-process") is shown in the
status bar.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interface " " \fIiface\fR
Open on the Connections tab and restrict it to flows on \fIiface\fR. May
be given more than once to show several interfaces. This filter is
transient (not saved) and mirrors
.BR iftop (8)'s
.BR \-i .
.TP
.B \-\-tray
Start with no main window \(em only the system\-tray icon with a live
throughput sparkline. Used by the XDG autostart entry installed from
.IR "Settings \(-> Tray \(-> Start on login" .
Click the tray icon to summon the window.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-agent
Skip the system\-bus agent and always use the in\-process backend. Intended
for development and debugging; needs root (or the self\-elevation prompt)
for per\-connection capture.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Print diagnostics to stderr (privilege escalation, backend errors, D\-Bus
probing).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show built\-in help and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.SH INTERFACE
Both tables are sortable by clicking a column header. The Connections view
accepts a filter expression (the same mini\-language documented in
.BR nqiftop (1));
right\-clicking a header toggles column visibility, and per\-column layout
plus the chosen view settings persist between runs. A row\-spanning gauge
tints each row in proportion to the loudest flow. Throughput is always
formatted in IEC units (KiB/s, MiB/s, ...).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/qiftop/qiftop.conf
Per\-user settings (\fBQSettings\fR INI): monitoring cadence, display
options, DNS, tray pins, autostart, and saved per\-column header state.
.TP
.I ~/.config/autostart/qiftop.desktop
XDG autostart entry, created/removed by the "Start on login" preference.
.SH SECURITY
Live per\-connection data is root\-only on most systems (the conntrack
table exposes every host's flows). Prefer running the unprivileged GUI
against
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
and joining the
.B netdev
group rather than running qiftop as root. See
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
for the agent's access model and the configurable process\-detail
disclosure policy.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nqiftop (1),
.BR qiftop\-agent (8),
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5),
.BR iftop (8),
.BR pkexec (1)
.SH HOMEPAGE
https://github.com/TheCleaners/qiftop
.SH BUGS
Report issues at https://github.com/TheCleaners/qiftop/issues
